= Count Ferdinand van der Heuvel

Count van der Heuvel is a seasoned bureaucrat whose career remembers times of Vizimir II the Just.

As a Minister of Civil Service he allows as to compromise with aristocracy to achieve some of our goals 

- cs_hiring
- cs_start_expansion
- cs_stop_expansion
- @main: Back

@carels
title: Otto Carels
is-pinned-card: true
view-if: cs_created = 1 and cs_minister = "Otto Carels"
tags: cabinet
card-image: img/carels.jpg
new-page: true

Otto Carels is a radical, who as a chief judge of Roggeveen tried to use city autonomy to protect victims of persecutions.

As a Minister of Civil Service he leads a crusade against racism and superstition in our state.

- cs_hiring
- cs_start_expansion
- cs_stop_expansion
- @main: Back

@start_expansion
title: Expansion Civil Service has to be continued
view-if: cs_expansion = 0
on-arrival: cs_expansion = 1

@stop_expansion
title: Expansion of Civil Service has 
view-if: cs_expansion = 1
on-arrival: cs_expansion = 0

@cs_hiring
title: Change hiring practices

- @cs_add_nobles: We should offer post to various nobles
- @cs_remove_nobles: We shouldn't pretend noble birth makes someone good bureaucrat 
- @cs_add_church: We should employ priests of Eternal Fire
- @cs_remove_church: We should get rid of the Eternal Fire clergy
- @cs_add_cities: We should ask city councils and guilds to lend us their men
- @cs_remove_cities: We won't pay extra for officials from cities and guilds any longer 
- @cs_add_soldiers: We should look amongst low-rank soldiers for ones with organisation skills
- @cs_remove_soldiers: We don't need rabble among our officials
- @main: We have to wait with further expansion

@cs_add_nobles
subtitle: This will increase opportunities for hiring, but decrease skills of our bureaucrats. Nobility will gain influence and satisfaction
view-if: cs_hire_nobles = 0 and mini_actions = 0
on-arrival: {!
    Q.cs_net_width += 1;
    Q.cs_skill -= 1;
    Q.cs_hire_nobles = 1
    Q.estates.aristocracy.inf += 3
    Q.estates.aristocracy.sat += 3
    Q.estates.pettynobility.inf += 3
    Q.estates.pettynobility.sat += 3
    Q.mini_actions += 1
!}
go-to: cs_expansion_choices

We will offer posts to second and third sons of various nobles. What they lack in education they make up in inherited virtue

@cs_remove_nobles
subtitle: This will decrease opportunities for hiring, but increase skills of our bureaucrats. Nobility will be dissatisfied
view-if: cs_hire_nobles = 1 and mini_actions = 0
on-arrival: {!
    Q.cs_net_width -= 1;
    Q.cs_skill += 1;
    Q.cs_hire_nobles = 0
    Q.estates.aristocracy.inf -= 2
    Q.estates.aristocracy.sat -= 6
    Q.estates.pettynobility.inf -= 2
    Q.estates.pettynobility.sat -= 6
    Q.mini_actions += 1
!}
go-to: cs_expansion_choices

We shouldn't pretend noble birth makes someone good bureaucrat 

@cs_add_church
subtitle: This will increase opportunities for hiring and skills of our bureaucrats. Church will gain influence and satisfaction and may interfere with our reforms 
view-if: cs_hire_church = 0 and mini_actions = 0
on-arrival: {!
    Q.cs_net_width += 1;
    Q.cs_skill += 1;
    Q.cs_hire_church = 1;
    Q.cs_loyalty -= 1;
    Q.estates.church.inf += 3;
    Q.estates.church.sat += 3
    Q.mini_actions += 1
!}
go-to: cs_expansion_choices

We will include priests and monks of Eternal Fire in the new apparatus. What they lack in loyalty they make up in piety

@cs_remove_church
subtitle: This will decrease opportunities for hiring and skills of our bureaucrats. Church will be dissatisfied
view-if: cs_hire_church = 1 and mini_actions = 0
on-arrival: {!
    Q.cs_net_width -= 1;
    Q.cs_skill -= 1;
    Q.cs_hire_church = 0;
    Q.cs_loyalty += 1;
    Q.estates.church.inf -= 2;
    Q.estates.church.sat -= 6
    Q.mini_actions += 1
!}
go-to: cs_expansion_choices

We should get rid of the Eternal Fire clergy in our Civil Service. 

@cs_add_cities
subtitle: This will increase opportunities for hiring, but slightly increase salaries of our bureaucrats. Guilds will gain influence and satisfaction
view-if: cs_hire_cities = 0 and mini_actions = 0
on-arrival: {!
    Q.cs_net_width += 1;
    Q.cs_salaries += 0.5;
    Q.cs_hire_gold = 2 * (2 + Q.cs_salaries);
    Q.cs_hire_cities = 1
    Q.estates.guilds.inf += 3;
    Q.estates.guilds.sat += 3
    Q.mini_actions += 1
!}
go-to: cs_expansion_choices

We will make a deal with bourgeoisie to hire some of their clerks. We will have to pay extra for it

@cs_remove_cities
subtitle: This will decrease opportunities for hiring, but slightly decrease salaries of our bureaucrats. Guilds will be dissatisfied
view-if: cs_hire_cities = 1 and mini_actions = 0
on-arrival: {!
    Q.cs_net_width -= 1;
    Q.cs_salaries -= 0.5;
    Q.cs_hire_gold = 2 * (2 + Q.cs_salaries);
    Q.cs_hire_cities = 0
    Q.estates.guilds.inf -= 2;
    Q.estates.guilds.sat -= 6
    Q.mini_actions += 1
!}
go-to: cs_expansion_choices

We won't pay extra for hiring officials from cities and guilds any longer 

@cs_add_soldiers
subtitle: This will increase opportunities for hiring, but nobility will be offended by including such rabble in our administration.
view-if: cs_hire_soldiers = 0 and mini_actions = 0
on-arrival: {!
    Q.cs_net_width += 1;
    Q.cs_hire_admin += 5;
    Q.cs_loyalty += 1
    Q.cs_hire_soldiers = 1
    Q.estates.aristocracy.sat -= 6
    Q.estates.pettynobility.sat -= 6
    Q.estates.peasants.sat += 3
    Q.mini_actions += 1
!}
go-to: cs_expansion_choices

We will recruit best and brightest veterans of the War, regardless of their birth 

@cs_remove_soldiers
subtitle: This will decrease opportunities for hiring, but nobility will be glad we ensured officials come from proper milieu.
view-if: cs_hire_soldiers = 1 and mini_actions = 0
on-arrival: {!
    Q.cs_net_width -= 1;
    Q.cs_hire_admin -= 5;
    Q.cs_loyalty -= 1
    Q.cs_hire_soldiers = 0
    Q.estates.aristocracy.sat += 3
    Q.estates.pettynobility.sat += 3
    Q.estates.peasants.sat -= 6
    Q.mini_actions += 1
!}
go-to: cs_expansion_choices

We don't need rabble among our officials


